    • parseIntRange

      public static ArrayList<Integer> parseIntRange(String place, String value, StringBuilder errors)
      expands an Integer range into a list of Integers
      The formats are:
      - just an integer
      - a comma-separated list of integers. Ex. 3,5,-10
      - a range from to to. Ex. 3 to 10
      - a range from to to step n. Ex: 3 to 10 step 2 The step must not be negative.
      Parameter:
      place - for error reporting
      value - a string to be parsed
      errors - for appending error messages
      Gibt zurück:
      the expanded integer list

    • parseIntRange

      public static it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.ints.IntArrayList parseIntRange(String value, StringBuilder errors)
      expands an Integer range into a list of Integers
      The formats of a range are:
      - just an integer
      - a comma-separated list of ranges. Ex. 3,5,-10
      - a range start to end. start ≤ end. Ex. 3 to 10.
      - a range start to end step n. Ex: 3 to 10 step 2 The step must not be negative.
      Double occurrences are removed.
      The final numbers are sorted in increasingly.
      Parameter:
      value - a string to be parsed
      errors - for appending error messages
      Gibt zurück:
      the expanded integer list

    • parseIntRange

      public static it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.ints.IntArrayList parseIntRange(String value, int minimum, StringBuilder errors)
      expands an Integer range into a list of Integers
      The formats of a range are:
      - just an integer
      - a comma-separated list of ranges. Ex. 3,5,-10
      - a range start to end. start ≤ end. Ex. 3 to 10.
      - a range start to end step n. Ex: 3 to 10 step 2 The step must not be negative.
      Double occurrences are removed.
      The final numbers are sorted in increasingly.
      Parameter:
      value - a string to be parsed
      minimum - the smallest allowed value.
      errors - for appending error messages
      Gibt zurück:
      the expanded integer list or null

      n - the limit
      tuple - the set, coded as long
      predicate - to be applied to a long-value
      tuples - the already checked subsets
      Gibt zurück:
      true if tuple is the maximal subset satisfying the predicate.
